# .env.example — environment template for this repo
#
# STATUS: this project currently needs NO environment variables.
# It is a 100% front-end static site (React + Vite, no backend, no API keys,
# no secrets). It builds and runs with zero configuration:
#
#   npm install && npm run dev
#
# So there is nothing to copy into a real `.env` today. This file exists only
# to document that fact and to give a starting point IF a backend/API is ever
# added later.
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If you ever DO add runtime config, note the Vite rule: only variables
# prefixed with VITE_ are exposed to the browser bundle. NEVER put a private
# secret in a VITE_ var — anything VITE_ is shipped to every visitor in plain
# text. Real secrets must live on a server/edge function, never in this app.
#
# Example (commented out — not used today):
# VITE_CONTACT_FORM_ENDPOINT=https://example.com/api/contact
# VITE_ANALYTICS_ID=
#
# Deploy: Netlify auto-builds `main`. If env vars are ever needed, set them in
# Netlify → Site settings → Environment variables (NOT committed here).
